<br>
I've enjoyed the class from day one.  My melee friends absolutely hate the fact that they can't travel, can't solo even a green mob without sitting forever afterward (or dying outright), can't escape a bad situation without sow, or do much of anything without a group.  The ability to do these things is a wonderful thing indeed.  <br>
<br>
So we can't find an experience group...big deal.  Single pull, no-risk, no-excitement groups are something that I yearn for? Not hardly.  There is nothing so pleasing as going into a place like Mistmoore the other night and seeing 2 or 3 supernova's going off at the same time and laying waste to the entire area.  <br>
<br>
Let the melee's have their single pull groups.  Nothing more exciting than turning auto attack on, and rotating clicks of taunt, bash, kick and disarm for hours.  Or sitting all night and clicking a healing spell every so often.  Yummy!  I'd rather have the pullers message be something like &quot;oooh this is one BIG pull...lock and load!&quot;  Or I'd rather have the challenge of pulling off a nice quad-kite, even considering the medding involved.  <br>
<br>
My 2 coppers.<br>
